			<description><![CDATA[<p>
This is a<strong> new</strong>&nbsp;position working with the latest web based technologies such as Node.JS, Express, Jade and AngularJS.</p>
<p>
We are looking for a team player who enjoys developing rich web applications and spending time with JavaScript, CSS3, HTML, etc.&nbsp; as you will be part of the presentation tier development team and will be responsible for upholding the in-house standards and developing the front-end tech that powers the next generation of our enterprise backup solution. This is also an opportunity to work with the latest web based technologies such as Node, AngularJS, responsive HTML5 &amp; CSS3 frameworks and d3 charts.</p>
<p>
<strong>Primary Responsibilities:</strong><br />
&bull; Create an application that enables users&rsquo; workflows and exceeds expectations<br />
&bull; Using the latest web standards and developer environment such as HTML5,&nbsp; CSS3, and Node JS, convert static design into a graceful user experience across platforms/browsers. You&#39;re not satisfied until it looks and functions beautifully and seamlessly.<br />
&bull; Write elegant, clean and legible front-end and back end JavaScript code<br />
&bull; Write tests and assist in troubleshooting quality assurance issues<br />
&bull; Work in an agile team to deliver on time<br />
&bull; Ask questions and conduct research to find solutions and options for problems that arise<br />
&bull; Gained knowledge of and practice with the latest trends and languages to inform product architectural decisions<br />
&bull; Be the go-to person for the modules of the product you own</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Qualifications:</strong><br />
&bull; 3+ years of UI development<br />
&bull; Expert understanding of HTML and CSS<br />
&bull; Strong understanding of JavaScript and Angular JS (or any equivalent Ajax library)<br />
&bull; Unit testing experience<br />
&bull; Collaborative problem solver<br />
&bull; Demonstrated passion for your work and results orientation<br />
&bull; Strong attention to detail and desire to make great UIs<br />
&bull; Experience working in agile teams or similar process<br />
&bull; Strong communications skills &ndash; written, oral, and presentations<br />
&bull; B.S in Computer Science or related field</p>
<p>
<br />
Candidates invited in for an interview will be required to conduct a group interview for 4 &ndash; 6 employees, which can be a selection of former UI projects, screenshots, or a hypothetical project which includes both the end result and your code.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p>
Local candidates only.</p>
<p>
Sepaton is an Equal Employment Opportunity employer that values the strength diversity brings to the workplace.<br />
Sepaton does not accept unsolicited Agency resumes. Sepaton will not pay fees to any third party agency or firm that does not have a signed &quot;Sepaton Agency Fee Agreement&quot;.<br />
