			<description><![CDATA[<p>
This is a green field opportunity!&nbsp; The Senior Developer will work on design and implementation efforts on a variety of exciting new projects in a highly collaborative, fast-paced environment. Responsibilities include&nbsp;designing, prototyping, and building innovative solutions to address emerging market needs for massively scalable enterprise data center environments.<br />
<br />
Working closely with other product developers, architects, and product managers, you will be part of a team designing and building a specific set of components that will be part of an innovative total software and hardware solution.<br />
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Primary Responsibilities</strong><br />
&bull; Teaming with senior architects to implement major components of a scalable file system;<br />
&bull; Rapidly prototyping using agile software development methods;<br />
&bull; Authoring detailed specifications to be used to drive the design;<br />
&bull; Defining and participating in the development of other &ldquo;whole product&rdquo; requirements such as systems management, testing tools, and documentation;<br />
&bull; Successfully communicating design rationale and implementation details to others inside and outside the organization.<br />
<br />
<strong>Key Qualifications</strong><br />
&bull; Bachelor&#39;s (master&#39;s preferred) degree in computer science, math or related field;<br />
&bull; 3+ years of experience in developing large enterprise software components;<br />
&bull; Solid Linux or Unix systems experience;<br />
&bull; Experience developing system-level components including multi-threading, sockets, and RPC;<br />
&bull; Extensive experience programming in C and/or C++;<br />
&bull; Excellent interpersonal and communication skills, both written and verbal;<br />
&bull; Ability to work both independently and collaboratively;<br />
&bull; Ability to prioritize and manage work to critical project timelines in a fast-paced environment;<br />
&bull; Must be organized, have an eye for detail, and be able to put ideas into a tangible form;<br />
&bull; Direct experience in file system development is preferred;<br />
&bull; Knowledge of massively scalable or traditional cluster implementations like gfs, hdfs, ceph, gpfs, lustre or stornext preferred.</p>
<p>
Local candidates only.</p>
<p>
Sepaton is an Equal Employment Opportunity employer that values the strength diversity brings to the workplace.<br />
Sepaton does not accept unsolicited Agency resumes. Sepaton will not pay fees to any third party agency or firm that does not have a signed &quot;Sepaton Agency Fee Agreement&quot;.</p>
